Node.Notes: Word usually refers to "field," but also used for regions/adjacent territory.
Not mentioned in Exodus in connection with departure from Egypt. A city in northeastern Egypt (Tanis in LXX and also known as Avaris). Possibly the same as Raamses/Rameses in ex1:11.
Formally, heap. Refers to a barrier/dam-wall to hold a body of water.
Literally, "strong ones," which most think refer to heavenly beings--thus angels (also supported by LXX).
Uncertain. Probably related to some idea of distress/hurt/sadness.
Assumes "he sent among them" from first clause in this verse.
Manhood/virility, in particular reproductive power in this context.
